    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's interesting how you say it's hard to argue against it being a right. so if that's the case, does that mean the people who want to keep everything private and market-based are basically just arguing against human rights? like, can their economic concerns even be considered a valid moral stance if it goes against someone's right to live and be healthy?",
